,"1415":"1415","1414":"1414","1502":"1502","1413":"1413","1369":"1369","1412":"1412","1379":"1379","1411":"1411","about 1416":"about 1416","1388":"1388","about 1413":"about 1413","1416":"1416",", Hertfordshire, England":"Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","Presteigne with Discoed, Radnorshire, Wales":"Presteigne, Radnorshire, Wales","Newton, Leicestershire, England":"Cold Newton, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Burghill","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Gloucestershire and Somerset): variant of   Burchell  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Burchell","meanings":["English: habitational name from Birchill in Derbyshire or Birchills in Staffordshire, both named in Old English with <i>birce</i> ‘birch’ + <i>hyll</i> ‘hill’."]}]},{"name":"Maud","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Medieval vernacular form of   Matilda .  This form was characteristically Low German (i.e. including medieval Dutch and Flemish). The wife of  William the Conqueror , who bore this name, was the daughter of  Baldwin , Count of Flanders. In Flemish and Dutch the letter <i>-t-</i> was generally lost when it occurred between vowels, giving forms such as <i>Ma(h)auld</i>. <i>Maud</i> or <i>Matilda</i> was also the name of the daughter (  1102–67 ) of  Henry I  of England; she was married early in life to the Holy Roman Emperor  Henry V , and later disputed the throne of England with her cousin  Stephen . In  1128  she married  Geoffrey , Count of Anjou. A medieval chronicler commented, ‘she was a good woman, but she had little bliss with him’. The name <i>Maud</i> became quite common in England in the 19th century, when its popularity was influenced in part by  Tennyson's  poem Maud, published in  1855 , but has not been much used since the early decades of the 20th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Maud Burghill was born in 1392, in Cold Newton, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom, her father, John Burghill, was 24 and her mother, Ann Bulfynche, was 13. She married Walter Weaver III in 1412, in Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died about 1416, in Presteigne, Radnorshire, Wales, at the age of 25."},"et":{"1392–about 1416":"1392–umbes 1416","1392–1416":"1392–1416","1411–Male":"1411–Surnud","1415–Male":"1415–Surnud","1440–1502":"1440–1502","1591–1591":"1591–1591","1388–1413":"1388–1413","1413–1503":"1413–1503","1369–1414":"1369–1414","1379–Female":"1379–Surnud","1440":"1440","May 1414":"mai 1414","1591":"1591","1392":"1392","1503":"1503","1415":"1415","1414":"1414","1502":"1502","1413":"1413","1369":"1369","1412":"1412","1379":"1379","1411":"1411","about 1416":"umbes 1416","1388":"1388","about 1413":"umbes 1413","1416":"1416",", Hertfordshire, England":"Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Presteigne with Discoed, Radnorshire, Wales":"Presteigne, Radnorshire, Wales","Newton, Leicestershire, England":"Cold Newton, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1392–about 1416":"1392–noin 1416","1392–1416":"1392–1416","1411–Male":"1411–Kuollut","1415–Male":"1415–Kuollut","1440–1502":"1440–1502","1591–1591":"1591–1591","1388–1413":"1388–1413","1413–1503":"1413–1503","1369–1414":"1369–1414","1379–Female":"1379–Kuollut","1440":"1440","May 1414":"toukokuu 1414","1591":"1591","1392":"1392","1503":"1503","1415":"1415","1414":"1414","1502":"1502","1413":"1413","1369":"1369","1412":"1412","1379":"1379","1411":"1411","about 1416":"noin 1416","1388":"1388","about 1413":"noin 1413","1416":"1416",", Hertfordshire, England":"Hertfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England","Presteigne with Discoed, Radnorshire, W